Ask HN: What do you wish was better in designer-developer interactions?
text:
I'm studying how developers and designers can work together. I am curious about what sources of friction developers see with the other side (and vice versa).

One problem I am seeing is the developer handoff. Often designers give developers a Figma file, which is constantly changing, so developers are not sure when a design is finalized.

What other issues do you face in your team?

Ask HN: Quora account deletion; at risk of LGBTQ persecution
text:
Hey HN, I really need to get in touch with someone at Quora who can expedite the deletion process of an account I no longer have access to. The longer the account is public, the higher I’m at risk for LGBTQ persecution in my home country.

When I was younger, I naively started a Quora account with my real name and photo attached. I posted answers that reveal my LGBTQ identity. Right now, I’m being recognized in my (conservative) community for an accomplishment. Someone reached out to me saying they’re confused by the posts in my Quora profile and how they go against my national identity and (assumed) religion. If the person chooses to share this profile with authorities, I’m at stake to be persecuted and possibly lose on scholarship money that helps me stay in the US. The profile page is a top search result for Googling my name, which makes me even more worried.

I don’t remember the email address associated with the account and I tried enumerating through all the emails I remember owning—to no avail.

I would appreciate all the help I can get to delete the account. Thank you all in advance.
